People wearing face masks wait for a bus at a bus stop in Jakarta, Indonesia, Nov. 5, 2021. Indonesia on Friday confirmed 518 new COVID-19 cases, raising its tally of infections to 4,247,320, according to the country's Health Ministry. (Xinhua/Zulkarnain) JAKARTA, Nov. 5 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia on Friday confirmed 518 new COVID-19 cases, raising its tally of infections to 4,247,320, according to the country's Health Ministry. The ministry reported that the death toll from the virus in the country rose by 19 to 143,519, while 648 more people recovered during the past 24 hours, bringing the total number of recoveries to 4,092,586. Indonesia started mass COVID-19 vaccinations on Jan. 13 after the authorities approved the emergency use of the Chinese Sinovac vaccine. More than 123.82 million people have received their first doses of vaccines, while over 77.68 million have taken the second doses. Indonesia has so far administered over 202.66 million doses, including the third booster jabs. Enditem  